{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"def6e81f-45d5-496c-b17e-b676b2216ea8","content":"**Yes, you will hit a compatibility issue.** MSTest v4 dropped support for `net6.0` and `net7.0` — only `net8.0+`, `net462`, and `uap10.0` are supported.\n\nYour project targets `net6.0`, so upgrading to MSTest v4 will fail. You need to **retarget to `net8.0` or later** first.\n\nYour test code itself (a simple `[TestClass]`/`[TestMethod]` with `Assert.IsTrue`) has no API-level issues with v4 — the only blocker is the TFM.\n\n**To upgrade**, you'd need to:\n1. Change `<TargetFramework>net6.0</TargetFramework>` → `net8.0` (or `net9.0`)\n2. Then update the MSTest package from `3.8.0` → `4.x`\n\nWould you like me to make these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e8ac246a-7ddd-49c8-8ceb-a1dc20d66199","outputTokens":228},"id":"8c2beabe-fa36-4818-837c-4861fd4aa072","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:01:08.579Z","parentId":"4312bfb7-0f62-498f-920f-be028db08136"}
